@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}datediff()@{ub} - Get the time between two dates 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}datediff(date1, date2)@{ub} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Calculates the time span in days between the two given dates. 
   If one date has an unspecified element (shown as @{b}??@{ub}) the element of 
   the other date will be used. Always the time span from @{b}date1@{ub} to @{b}date2@{ub} 
   will be calculated. If @{b}date2@{ub} is before @{b}date1@{ub}, a negative result will 
   be returned. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}date1, date2@{ub} - two date strings 

@{b}Result:@{ub} Number of days between the two dates. 


@endnode 
