@node func_printf "printf()" 
@toc FuncRef

@{b}@{u}printf()@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}printf()@{ub} - Create a formatted string 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}printf(formatstring, ...)@{ub} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Formats the data specified as arguments according to the 
   formatting rules specified in @{b}formatstring@{ub}. Formatstring is a string, 
   that may contain control sequences that will be replaced by formatted 
   data that have been specified as arguments. All control sequences are 
   introduced by a percent sign. A control sequence has the format 
   (fields in brackets are optional):
   @{b}%[flags][width][.precision]type@{ub}
   The arguments are associated with the 
   control sequences using the order. 

@{b}Flags:@{ub} can be one of the following:
   @{b}-@{ub} the result will be left-justified within the width
   @{b}+@{ub} If specified, a plus sign will be added before a positive number
   @{b}0@{ub} The with of the field will be padded with zeros if it is a 
   number 

@{b}Width:@{ub} The width is the minimum number of characters that this formatting 
   item should use. 

@{b}Precision:@{ub} A whole number. The precision of the output, depending of the 
   type of the control sequence:
   @{b}d,u,o,x,X@{ub} - minimum number of digits
   @{b}e,f@{ub} - number of digits after of decimal point
   @{b}g@{ub} - maximum number of significant digits
   @{b}s@{ub} - maximum length of the string to be copied
   

@{b}Type:@{ub} can be one of the following:
   @{b}c@{ub} - One character of the specified ASCII value will be generated.
   @{b}d@{ub} - A signed integer value will be generated.
   @{b}u@{ub} - An unsigned integer value will be generated. 
   @{b}o@{ub} - An octal number will be generated. 
   @{b}x@{ub} - A hexadecimal number will be generated. The characters a-f will be lowercase.
   @{b}X@{ub} - A hexadecimal number will be generated. The characters 
   a-f will be uppercase.
   @{b}e@{ub} - A fractional number with the format d.dde-ddd will be generated.
   @{b}f@{ub} - A fractional number with the format dd.dd will be generated.
   @{b}g@{ub} - A fractional number will be generated. The format will 
   be chosen according to the magnitude of the number.
   @{b}s@{ub} - A string will be inserted. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} The formatstring and the further arguments for the 
   formatstring. 

@{b}Result:@{ub} A formatted string 


@endnode 
@node func_rand "rand()" 
@toc FuncRef

@{b}@{u}rand()@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}rand()@{ub} - random number generator 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}rand()@{ub} 

@{b}Functions:@{ub} Returns a random number. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} none 

@{b}Result:@{ub} A fractional random number. @{b}0.0 <= r < 1.0@{ub}. 


@endnode  
@node func_right "right()" 
@toc FuncRef

@{b}@{u}right()@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}right()@{ub} - Get the right part of a string 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}right(string, length)@{ub} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Returns the right part of a string with the specified length. 
   If length is greater than the real length of the string, the whole 
   string will be returned. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}string@{ub} - string to be scanned
   @{b}length@{ub} - length of the part to be returned 

@{b}Result:@{ub} A substring of string 


@endnode 
@node func_round "round()" 
@toc FuncRef

@{b}@{u}round()@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}round()@{ub} - rounding 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}round(value)@{ub} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Returns a mathematically rounded number of @{b}value@{ub}. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}value@{ub} - real number 

@{b}Result:@{ub} a whole number 


@endnode 
@node func_second "second()" 
