@node func_strcat "strcat()" 
@toc FuncRef

@{b}@{u}strcat()@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}strcat()@{ub} - Concatenate strings 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}strcat(string1, string2, ...)@{ub} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Concatenates two or more strings to one string, that is 
   returned. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}string1 ... stringn@{ub} - The strings to be concatenated. At least 
   two, no maximum. 

@{b}Result:@{ub} The concatenated string. 


@endnode 
@node func_strcmp "strcmp()" 
@toc FuncRef

@{b}@{u}strcmp()@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}strcmp()@{ub} - Compare two strings 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}strcmp(string1, string2)@{ub} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Checks whether the specified strings are equal. The comparision 
   is done case sensitive, i.e. also the case of the strings has to be 
   equal when the two strings should be considered equal. A case 
   insensitive comparision can be done with @{b}@{"stricmp" Link func_stricmp}@{ub}. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}string1, string2{} - strings to be compared 

@{b}Result:@{ub} 0 if both strings are equal, -1 if @{b}string1@{ub} < @{b}string2@{ub} and +1 if 
   @{b}string1@{ub} > @{b}string2@{ub} 


@endnode 
@node func_stricmp "stricmp()" 
@toc FuncRef

@{b}@{u}stricmp()@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}stricmp()@{ub} - Compare two strings 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}stricmp(string1, string2)@{ub} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Checks, whether the specified strings are equal or not. The 
   comparision is done case insensitive, i.e. the case of the strings 
   does not matter during comparision. A case sensitive comparision can 
   be done with @{b}@{"strcmp" Link func_stricmp}@{ub}. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}string1, string2{} - strings to be compared 

@{b}Result:@{ub} 0 if both strings are equal, -1 if @{b}string1@{ub} < @{b}string2@{ub} and +1 if 
   @{b}string1@{ub} > @{b}string2@{ub} 


@endnode 
@node func_strlen "strlen()" 
@toc FuncRef

@{b}@{u}strlen()@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}strlen()@{ub} - Length of a string. 

