@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}OpenServiceWindow@{ub} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Opens the @{"service window" Link ServiceWin}, if it is not already open. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} None. 

@{b}Results:@{ub} None. 


@endnode 
@node rxpasterecord "PasteRecord" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}PasteRecord@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}PasteRecord@{ub} -- Paste a record from the clipboard 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}PasteRecord Record/K/N,Unit/K/N,Inactive/S@{ub}
   @{b}RC@{ub} = @{i}Success@{ui} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Inserts a record from the clipboard into the addressed Fiasco 
   database. The record may be written to the clipboard by @{b}@{"CopyRecord" Link rxcopyrecord}@{ub} or @{b}
   @{"CutRecord" Link rxcutrecord}@{ub}.  This command may be only called in record mode. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}Record@{ub} - Number of record after which the new record will be 
   inserted. Default: the active record. 
   @{b}Unit@{ub} - Number of clipboard unit. Default: 0. 
   @{b}Inactive@{ub} - Do not activate the new record. 
   

@{b}Results:@{ub} @{b}RC@{ub} - Success 


@endnode 


@node rxprogress "Progress" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}Progress@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}Progress@{ub} -- Show a progress bar 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}Progress Done/A/N,Max/A/N@{ub}
   @{b}RC@{ub} = @{i}Success@{ui} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Displays a nice progress bar in the service window, as known of 
   Sort or Open Project. You should reset the status gadget with @{b}
   @{"ResetStatus" Link rxResetStatus}@{ub} when the operation has completed.  

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}Done@{ub} -- the number of data items currently processed. 
   @{b}Max@{ub} -- the number of all data items. 

@{b}Results:@{ub} None. 


@endnode 


@node rxquit "Quit" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}Quit@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}Quit@{ub} -- Exit Fiasco 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}Quit@{ub} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Closes all databases and exits Fiasco. No warnings will be 
   done. After this command you cannot access any ARexx ports of Fiasco. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} None. 

@{b}Results:@{ub} None. 


@endnode 
@node rxreadsettings "ReadSettings" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}ReadSettings@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}ReadSettings@{ub} -- Read Fiasco settings (8)

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}ReadSettings File/A@{ub}
   @{b}RC@{ub} = @{i}Success@{ui} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Reads Fiasco settings from the specified file and activates 
   these settings. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}File@{ub} - File to read Fiasco settings from. 

@{b}Results:@{ub} @{b}RC@{ub} - Success 


@endnode 
@node rxrecompileformulas "RecompileFormulas" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}RecompileFormulas@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}RecompileFormulas@{ub} - Update all formulas (7)

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}RecompileFormulas@{ub}
   @{b}RC@{ub} = @{i}Success@{ui} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Recompiles (i.e. updates) all formulas in the addressed 
   database. This especially useful after a call to @{b}@{"SetConstant" link rxsetconstant}@{ub}. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} None. 

@{b}Results:@{ub} @{b}RC@{ub} - Success. 


@endnode 
@node rxrequestchoice "RequestChoice" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}RequestChoice@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}RequestChoice@{ub} - Request a choice from the user 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}RequestChoice Body/A,Gadgets/A,Title/K,Var/K@{ub}
   @{b}RC@{ub} = @{i}Success@{ui} 
   @{b}Result@{ub} = @{i}Choice@{ui} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Creates an intuition easy-requester with the specified 
   parameters. Works very similar to the CLI command @{b}Requestchoice@{ub}. The 
   differences: Slightly different parameters, puts the requester up on 
   Fiasco's screen. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}Body@{ub} - Main text of requester.
   @{b}Gadgets@{ub} - Gadgets at the bottom of requester. Each choice 
   must be separated by a |.
   @{b}Title@{ub} - Title of requester. 

@{b}Results:@{ub} @{b}RC@{ub} - Success.
   @{b}Result@{ub} - Number of selected gadget, 0 for the rightmost one. 


@endnode 
@node rxrequestfield "RequestField" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}RequestField@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}RequestField@{ub} - Request a field from the user 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}RequestField Default/K,Text/A,Var/K@{ub}
   @{b}RC@{ub} = @{i}Success@{ui}
   @{b}Result@{ub} = @{i}Selected field@{ui} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Opens a requester with a list of all fields of the adressed 
   project. The requester can display an additional message given in the 
   @{b}Text@{ub} argument. The user can select one field and click on @{b}Ok@{ub} or can 
   @{b}Cancel@{ub} the requester. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}Default@{ub} - The field that will be selected when the requester opens.
   @{b}Text@{ub} - The text to be displayed. 

@{b}Results:@{ub} @{b}RC@{ub} - Success. Will be 5 if user cancelled requester.
   @{b}Result@{ub} - ID of the selected field. 


@endnode 
@node rxrequestfile "RequestFile" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}RequestFile@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}RequestFile@{ub} -- Open a file requester 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}RequestFile File,Pattern/K,Title/K,SaveMode/S,DrawersOnly/S,NoIcons/S,
   ProjectRelative/S,Var/K@{ub}
   @{b}RC@{ub} = @{i}Success@{ui}
   @{b}Result@{ub} = @{i}Selected file@{ui} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Puts up an ASL file requester. Works very similar to the CLI 
   command @{b}Requestfile@{ub}. The differences: Slightly different parameters, 
   puts the requester up on Fiasco's screen. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}File@{ub} - Initial File including path for the requester
   @{b}Pattern@{ub} - Initial Pattern
   @{b}Title@{ub} - Title for the requester
   @{b}SaveMode@{ub} - Activates savemode: Black background, no selection 
   via doubleclick
   @{b}DrawersOnly@{ub} - Displays only Drawers 
   @{b}NoIcons@{ub} - Filters Icons 
   @{b}ProjectRelative@{ub} - The requested file will be relative to the addressed 
   database. 

@{b}Results:@{ub} @{b}RC@{ub} - Success. Will be 5 if user cancelled requester. 
   @{b}Result@{ub} - Selected file. 


@endnode 
@node rxrequestnumber "RequestNumber" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}RequestNumber@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}RequestNumber@{ub} -- Request a number 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}RequestNumber Default/K/N,Title/K,Text/K/A,Var/K@{ub}
   @{b}RC@{ub} = @{i}Success@{ui}
   @{b}Result@{ub} = @{i}Requested number@{ui} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Asks the user to input an integer number. He may cancel the 
   request. You can supply additional information using the @{b}Text@{ub} 
   argument.  

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}DefaultValue@{ub} - Value of integer gadget on startup. Will be 
   zero if not specified.
   @{b}Title@{ub} - Optional. Window title of requester.
   @{b}Text@{ub} - Additional text to display in requester. May contain 
   newlines @{b}(*n)@{ub}. Please note that this argument is required and must be 
   specified with a leading keyword. This is for compability with future 
   versions of Fiasco which may not require the @{b}Text@{ub} argument. 

@{b}Results:@{ub} @{b}RC@{ub} - Success. Will be 5 if user cancelled requester.
   @{b}Result@{ub} - Requested number. 


@endnode 


@node rxrequeststring "RequestString" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}RequestString@{ub}@{uu}


