@node rxsaveas "SaveAs" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}SaveAs@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}SaveAs@{ub} -- Save a Fiasco database under a new name. 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}SaveAs Name/K@{ub} 
   @{b}RC@{ub} = @{i}Success@{ui} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Saves the addressed database under a given name on disk. If you 
   specify a new name after the @{b}Name@{ub} keyword, this name will be used. If 
   you do not specify @{b}Name@{ub}, the user will be prompted with a file 
   requester to specify a new name. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}Name@{ub} - New file name. If not specified, a file requester will 
   be opened. 

@{b}Results:@{ub} @{b}RC@{ub} - Success. 


