@node rxsavesettings "SaveSettings" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}SaveSettings@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}SaveSettings@{ub} -- Save Fiasco settings (8)

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}SaveSettings File/A@{ub}
   @{b}RC@{ub} = @{i}Success@{ui} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Saves the active Fiasco settings to the specified file. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}File@{ub} - File to save the settings to. 

@{b}Results:@{ub} @{b}RC@{ub} - Success 


@endnode 
@node rxsetattr "SetAttr" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}SetAttr@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}SetAttr@{ub} -- Set an Fiasco attribute 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}SetAttr Object/A,Name/K,Attribute,Value/A@{ub}
   @{b}RC@{ub} = @{i}Success@{ui} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Sets the specified attribute. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}Object@{ub} - Object type to be set.
   @{b}Name@{ub} - Some object types require a name to be specified.
   @{b}Attribute@{ub} - Name of attribute to be set.
   @{b}Value@{ub} - New value for attribute. 

@{b}Results:@{ub} @{b}RC@{ub} - Success.
   

@{b}Objects:@{ub} @{b}Field@{ub} - Data related to a Fiasco field in the addressed 
   database. Name required. May be only used in mask mode. 

@{b}Attributes for Field:@{ub} @{b}Left@{ub} - Left edge of field. 
   @{b}Top@{ub} - Top edge of field. 
   @{b}Width@{ub} - Width of field. 
   @{b}Height@{ub} - Height of field. 
   @{b}ARexxScript@{ub} - ARexx script of field. 
   @{b}PickerARexx@{ub} - ARexx script for picker button.
   @{b}Formula@{ub} - Formula for field.
   @{b}ListLeft@{ub} - Left edge in list window.
   @{b}ListWidth@{ub} - Width in list window.
   @{b}Shortcut@{ub} - Keyboard shortcut for field.
   @{b}InitContType@{ub} - Type of initial content. One of @{b}LAST@{ub}, @{b}KEY@{ub} or @{b}OWN@{ub}. 
   @{b}InitContValue@{ub} - Value of initial content.
   @{b}MaxChars@{ub} - Max chars of field. Not supported by all fields.
   @{b}MinValue@{ub} - Minimum value of field. Not supported by all fields.
   @{b}MaxValue@{ub} - Maximum value of field. Not supported by all fields.
   @{b}Format@{ub} - Format of field. Not supported by all fields.
   @{b}Precision@{ub} - Precision of field. Not supported by all fields.
   @{b}Command@{ub} - Command for field. Not supported by all fields.
   @{b}Stack@{ub} - Stack for field. Not supported by all fields.
   @{b}Virtual@{ub} - Status of virtual flag of field. 1 or 0. 
   @{b}ListHidden@{ub} - Is field hidden in the list? 1 or 0. 
   @{b}Hidden@{ub} - Is field hidden in the mask? 1 or 0. 
   @{b}ReadOnly@{ub} - Is field read only? 1 or 0. 
   


@endnode 
@node rxsetconstant "SetConstant" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}SetConstant@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}SetConstant@{ub} - Set a constant (7)

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}SetConstant Name/A,Value/A/F@{ub}
   @{b}RC@{ub} = @{i}Success@{ui} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Sets a constant to the specified value in the addressed 
   project. If a constant of the same name already exists, it will be 
   overwritten, otherwise a new constant will be created.  Constants are 
   most commonly used in Fiasco formulas, but may be also used for other 
   purposes. The user may view and change the constants of a database 
   using the @{"Constants requester" Link rqconstants}.  If the formulas of the database are 
   supposed to use the new or changed constant, you have to call @{b}
   @{"RecompileFormulas" Link rxrecompileformulas}@{ub} after this command. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}Name@{ub} - Name of the constant to set.
   @{b}Value@{ub} - Value for the constant. 

@{b}Results:@{ub} @{b}RC@{ub} - Success. 


@endnode 


@node rxsetfield "SetField" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}SetField@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}SetField@{ub} - Set the content of a field 

@{b}Synopsis:@{ub} @{b}SetField FieldID,Record/K/N,ListEntry/K/N,CreateListEntries/S, 
   ExtFormat/S,Stem/K,Cont/F@{ub} 
   @{b}RC@{ub} = @{i}Success@{ui} 

@{b}Function:@{ub} Sets the content of the specified field in the active or 
   specified record to the specified content.  If @{b}Stem@{ub} is used, Fiasco 
   will copy the values of the ARexx variables with the names 
   @{i}stemname@{ui}.@{i}fieldID@{ui} to the respective fields. If a variable is not set, 
   the field will not be changed. Useful with @{b}@{"GetField Stem" Link rxgetfield}@{ub} see there for 
   a description.  Entries in listview fields are normally neither 
   created, nor removed by this command. Thus, if you have a listview 
   field with three entries and you call @{b}SetField Stem MyStem@{ub} with @{b}MyStem@{ub} 
   initialized with four entries for the listview field, only the first 
   three will be copied and the fourth entry will be ignored. If you have 
   initialized @{b}MyStem@{ub} to contain less entries for the listview than it 
   contains, the last entries in the listview will be left unchanged. 
   However, if you use the @{b}CreateListEntries@{ub} switch, this command will 
   remove all old entries from the listview and replace them by the 
   entries in the stem variable.    This command may be only called in 
   record mode. 

@{b}Arguments:@{ub} @{b}FieldID@{ub} - ID of a single field to be set
   @{b}Record@{ub} - Number of record
   @{b}ListEntry@{ub} - Only if field is a listview field. Number of the 
   entry in the listview to be set to the new value. Counting from 1.
   @{b}CreateListEntries@{ub} - See above for explanation. Only in combination 
   with @{b}Stem@{ub}. New in Fiasco 2.2.
   @{b}ExtFormat@{ub} - If specified, @{b}SetField@{ub} uses the extended format that 
   is returned by @{b}@{"GetField ExtFormat" Link rxgetfield}@{ub}. New in Fiasco 2.2. @{b}Cont@{ub} - New 
   content of the field. This argument takes the whole input inclusive 
   spaces. The interpretation of this arg depends on the fieldtype (In 
   brackets: @{b}ExtFormat@{ub}): 
   String - is copied directly 
   Integer - Numbers are read directly, other things are 0 
   Float - dto. 
   Boolean - 1 or TRUE = selected, 0 or FALSE = not selected 
   Slider - Number is read. Bad numbers will be adjusted. 
   Cycle - Number or name of label is taken. 
   Date - Date in the format DD.MM.[YY]YY (current locale format) 
   Time - Time in the format HH:MM:SS (current locale format) 
   Extern - is copied directly 
   Datat. - is copied directly 
   Var String - is copied directly. The string @{b}*n@{ub} will be converted to a 
   line break. This works, however, only if the string is enclosed in 
   quotes. 
    If the field is a listview field, use @{b}ListEntry@{ub} to set the content of 
   a particular entry. Use the format of the underlying fieldtype. To add 
   entries to listviews, either use the @{b}CreateListEntries@{ub} switch or use @{b}
   @{"AddLVFieldEntry" Link rxAddLVFieldEntry}@{ub}.  

@{b}Results:@{ub} @{b}RC@{ub} - Success 

@{b}Notes:@{ub} Before release 2.2, this document claimed that the date and time 
   field data would be required in the current locale format. However, it 
   has always been the case, that - if @{b}ExtFormat@{ub} is not specified - these 
   values are formatted independantly from the locale setting.  


@endnode 


@node rxsetmode "SetMode" 
@toc ARexxFuncInd

@{b}@{u}SetMode@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name:@{ub} @{b}SetMode@{ub} - Set the working mode 

